course_aims:
The main aims of this course are to enable students to:

A. Appreciate how different levels of control between entities affects the required accounting treatment of them and to be able to apply the appropriate accounting treatment;

B. Develop an ability to link a variety of concepts in corporate accounting, displaying a wider appreciation of the complexity and inter-relatedness of the concepts;

C. Achieve awareness of current developments in accounting standards through research and critical evaluation to interpret and communicate their effect on entities; and

D. Relate core concepts to real world scenarios, developing an awareness of how reporting entities adopt these concepts and if there are any ethical issues.
